Why Logs Matter?
Logs help identify failures and troubleshoot issues.

View Logs:
cat /var/log/syslog

View Last Lines:
tail -f /var/log/syslog

Search Logs:
grep ERROR application.log

View Journal Logs:
journalctl -u nginx

Today's Logs:
journalctl --since today

Real-Time Scenario:
Jenkins not starting.
journalctl -xeu jenkins

This is one of the most important commands for DevOps engineers.
